<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-181-402  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 181 402.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 10 1989 n243 p40(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Carriers eager to expand T1-pipe intelligence. (communications)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roeckl, Chris.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Common carriers are adding such features as diagnosticinformation, bandwidth provisions, automatic rerouting and moreintelligence to the T1 pipe in an effort to bring serviceofferings back into the central office.andP;  MCI plans to deploy 33digital access and cross-connect systems within their network toreroute circuits more quickly in the case of a network outage.andP;  ATand T is installing extended superframe formatting throughout itsAccunet T1.5 network to address users' needs for network control.andO;A vertical systems analyst, David Marble, calls the T1 network ofthe future the Central Office-Based Intelligent Transport (COBIT),which he envisions as a set of carrier services that would providefunctions similar to those offered in a private network.andP;  COBITwould give back some of the account control to carriers andimprove revenues from T1 services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     T1 CommunicationsCommon CarriersCommunications TechnologyCommunications IndustryEnhancementsTransmission LinesMarketingAnalysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>